7. For, there are alwayes, two Kingdomes in the Four Elements, underſtood; Firſt; according to Gods out poured Love; and ſecondly according to his Anger: Yet they dwell only in the part of the Anger; 

                              •
                           nd are locked up in the Eternall Night, and are not able to touch the Good Power of the Elements.

1. JOhn the Firſt Chapter, verſe 11, 12, 13. It is written. Verſe 11. HE (JESUS CHRIST) came Or unto. into his own, and his own received him not:
Verſe 12. But ſo many as received him, to them he gave power to become the Children of God, which believe in his Name;
Verſe 13. which are generated or born not of Bloud, nor of the Will of the Fleſh; nor of the Will of a Man, but of God, &c.
